applicationProfileDefinition.en: Abstract class of all names in a namespace.
Shape and position characteristics of an object.

vocabularyDefinition.en: The way the geometry was determined.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: The way the geometry was determined.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Datatype is DomainObject, to be substituted by Geometry or its subclasses or by Temporal Entity or subclasses thereof.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Information used to uniquely identify an object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: The starting point here is that this string is assigned by an organization and that this is done according to a well-defined system.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Link to the agent that issued the identifier.
Name of the agent who assigned the identifier.
Time when the identifier was issued.
String used to uniquely identify the object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Type of string refers to the identification system (including its version), the string itself to the actual identifier.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Indication of a geographical position, by means of coordinates, a toponym, an address label, a reference to a city/region or reference to an address.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Essentially a value and the name of the type of value. In this context, it is about things such as operator, ambient temperature, etc.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Name of the type of value.
Qualitative or quantitative interpretation of the value.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: The Any data type should be replaced by something more concrete such as Agent or Measure.
Datatype is typically a URI. NOTE: More information about this data type can be found in ISO 19103 Geographic Information - Conceptual schema language.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Information about the operations that took place on the data or the source data that was used in producing the data.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: NOTE: More information about this data type can be found in ISO 19115 Geographic Information - Metadata.

vocabularyDefinition.en: Geometry of the Point Value Pair.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Geometry of the Point Value Pair.
Accuracy of the position of the data in a spatial reference system.
Observations whose results are somehow related.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: It is about coherence that is important to understand the result of individual observations, e.g. biotic relationships (animal A is predator and is present because animal B is prey). Such relationships require to be explicitly described (as opposed to relationships such as the coincidence of results of Observations in space or time that may remain implicit). Also useful for relationships where the output of Observation A is the input for Observation B.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Other Sampling Object to which the Sampling Object is associated.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. Sampling Points along a Sampling Curve or Samples taken at a Sampling Point or sub-samples (Sample of a Sample)...

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Link to the agent that issued the identifier.
Name of the agent who assigned the identifier.
Time when the identifier was issued.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Typically the place where the sample is stored (possibly up to the level of the shelf or drawer in the magazine).
Specifically, the discrete part of the range for which the value of the phenomenon is known. E.g. a measuring point and the value in that measuring point.
Specifically, the discrete part of the range for which the value of the phenomenon is known. E.g. a pixel and the value of the pixel.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Geometry of the Spatial Sampling Object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Datatype is DomainObject, to be substituted by Geometry or its subclasses or by Temporal Entity or subclasses thereof.

vocabularyDefinition.en: Geometry of the Point Value Pair.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Geometry of the Point Value Pair.
Procedure or instrument installed in or on the Spatial Sampling Object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. a procedure of type "Monitoring Water Quality" that is continuously carried out in a measuring station or a device of type "Anemometer" that is installed there.

vocabularyDefinition.en: The person or thing that serves to establish the observation.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: The person or thing that serves to establish the observation.
Reference to the information that uniquely identifies the Sampling Object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. the unique number assigned to a Sample or the number of a measuring station.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: String used to uniquely identify the object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Type of string refers to the identification system (including its version), the string itself to the actual identifier.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Nature of the material of which the Sample is composed.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: According to a basic classification, e.g. soil, water, stone, liquid, liquid, dust, vegetable, food.

vocabularyDefinition.en: The way the geometry was determined.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: The way the geometry was determined.
Data that contains information about data.
Moment when the preparation takes place.
Name of the type of value.
Reference to the Origin of a Sampling Object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: The Provenance describes the origin and history of the Sampling Object. E.g. the method of sampling or the method followed in a field study.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Arbitrary data associated with the event of the Observation.
Random data associated with the Sampling Object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. a parameter that describes an aspect of the Sampling (e.g. height during an air survey) or an important environmental parameter (e.g. the water level during a borehole).

applicationProfileDefinition.en: The moment at which the result of the Observation was applicable.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: Typically the moment when observation or sampling took place. If the Observation is temporal and the moment at which something takes place is registered, then this is also the phenomenon time.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Accuracy with which the geometry is determined.
The value of the observed Attribute as a result of the Observation.
Result of the Point Range Observation.
Result of the Time Series Observation.
Extent to which the result of the Observation meets the requirements or expectations.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: These are data that are specific to the Observation and complementary to the description of the procedure followed in the Observation (method of analysis, etc., see class Process), which in itself also says something about the quality of the result.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Time at which the result of the Observation was obtained.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. Observation A "isInputFor" Observation B, Observation A "explains" the result of Observation B.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Form in which the Monster was obtained;

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. drill core, solution, pulp, disc etc.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Manner in which the Sample was obtained from the sampled Object.
Manner in which the Sample was obtained from the sampled Object.
Location where the Sample was taken.
Time when the sample was obtained from the sampled object.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. length, mass, volume etc depending on the nature of the sample.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Period for which the result of the Observation applies.
Qualitative or quantitative interpretation of the value.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: The Any data type should be replaced by something more concrete such as Agent or Measure.

vocabularyDefinition.en: Assignment in the context of which the Observation takes place.

applicationProfileDefinition.en: Assignment in the context of which the Observation takes place.

applicationProfileUsageNote.en: E.g. the Assignment for a field survey or for the performance of specific Measurements or analyses of a Sample.
